dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.1: Active Login Customer: Customers with login behavior during screening period are defined as active login customers; login behavior includes the login of transaction systems such as trader terminal MT4/5 or cTrader.
dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.2: Active trading customers: customers who have trading behavior during screening period are defined as active trading customers; trading behavior includes open orders, close orders and pend orders.
dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.7: Customer to be activated: Customer registered with the trader terminal who only opened an account, deposit, and without any other operations, it is defined as the customer to be activated.
dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.8: This indicator can reflect the quality of new customers and the matchability of target customers and the platform.
dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.9: Sleeping customers: No login behavior (including Trader work, MT4, MT5, cTrader login) within 90 days, no deposit and withdrawal activity, no order related operations such as open order, close order, pend order, modify stop loss and take profit. Account registration time less than 90 days is not included in this case.
dashboard.CustomerAnalysis.11: Transaction Number Calculating Method: Open or close order is count as one time respectively. According to the first six letters of the symbol code, it will be deifned as the same symbol if the first six letters are matched, the same symbols will be combined for calculating the number of transactions.
